Sentencas: Reduced-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), featuring thin strontium-and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate (LSGM) electrolytes and nano-scale Ni anodes, showed high power densities of 1.20 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C and 0.39 W cm(-2) at 550 degrees C when operated on humidified hydrogen fuel and air oxidant.
Titulo: A reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell with nanostructured anodes
